nodes.html: Will you stand with Thorne and demand justice?

nodes.html: Have you or someone you know been injured by Jared Polis and others as described in Thorne’s Complaint ?

nodes.html: • Scroll down the following list and select the county in which you work or have a residence.

nodes.html: • Repeat the following process for each Complaint.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Print a hard copy of each entire eight page Complaint.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Carefully read the entire Complaint, especially the 8th page that you are going to sign in front of the notary, but do not sign page 8 yet.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Notice in the top half of page 1 of the Complaint, there is contact information for the Attorney General and District Attorney, including the mailing and email address.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Take the hard copy of each entire eight page Complaint and your photo identification to a notary public.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Tell the notary public you want to sign an Affidavit for them to notarize (page 8).

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • When the notary public asks you for it, present your photo identification to confirm your identity.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • When the notary public tells you to do so, print your full name in the blank at the top of page 8 of the Complaint, then sign it at the bottom of page 8, and then the notary public will sign and stamp it.

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Scan each Complaint, including your signed and notarized page, into a PDF formatted digital file (1 pdf file for each Complaint).

none.message: Element does not duplicate existing text in alt text

nodes.html: • Email the Complaint to the Attorney General and/or District Attorney at the email address (if any) you will find on page 1 of the Complaint.
